                     <origDate notBefore="1690" notAfter="1706">The name of King ʾIyasu I (r.
                        1682-1706) is mentioned throughout the Ms. The name of the original donor,
                        Tälawe Krǝstos, is known in connection with King ʾIyasu I. &#xD; Additio 12
                        mentions rās Sǝbḥāt (ʾAragāwi, governor of Tǝgray in the years 1892-95 and
                        1908-14).</origDate>
                  </origin>
               <provenance>The name of the original donor Tälawe Krǝstos
                        (226vb), has been erased throughout the Ms
                     (sometimes the first letter of his name remained, e.g. 69vb l.14).&#xD; According to Additio 12, the Ms. was bought by
                     priests ʾabuna Walda Mikāʾel and his son
                        ʾabuna Takla Hāymānot and donated to the
                     church of Yoḥannǝs Maṭmǝq Dǝbla. The names of the donors, and other names (of
                     their relatives?), are written in the supplication formulas in a recent hand:
                     Walda Mikāʾel (e.g., 4ra, 5rc, 5vc), Takla
                     Hāymānot (3ra, 5va, 6rc), (ʾAmata) Ṣädalä Māryām
                        (6ra, 32ra, 57va), Walatta Kidān (31va, 68vc, 172vc), Walda Yoḥannǝs (82ra, 87ra, 88rc), Gabra ʾAragāwi (82ra, 91ra, 129vc), Gabra Yoḥannǝs (84rb), Mazgaba Śǝllāse (151ra, 152rc, 156ra), Walda Giyorgis (172vb, 182rc, 191vb), Gabra ʾƎgziʾabǝḥer (198vc, 208ra, 209rc).&#xD; &#xD; The same names are indicated in
                     Ms. DMD-009; some of the names are found in Ms. DMD-012.</provenance></history>
